Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways and scoop out
the seeds. Chop it widthways into 2cm slices, then chop into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!).
Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then
chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine and butternut onto a large #roasting tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and
sprinkle over the @baharat spice mix{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat,
then arrange in a single layer.

> You might need to use two roasting trays, you want everything nicely spaced out.

Roast until golden brown and cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Halve, peel and cut the @red onion{1} into 2cm wide wedges. When you turn the roasting
vegetables, add the onion wedges and stir through. Return to the oven for the remaining
cooking time.

Meanwhile, crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into small chunks. Pop the @Greek style
flatbreads{4} onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}.

About ~{5%minutes} before the vegetables are done, add the @fig jam{40%g} to the roasted
vegetables and mix well to coat all the veggies. Return to the oven with the flatbreads
on the middle shelf for a further ~{5%minutes}.

Divide the flatbreads between plates and top with the roasted vegetables. Top with the
@wild rocket{40%g} and crumbled feta with a drizzle of olive oil over the top. Enjoy!